Kwale Governor Salim Mvurya’s mother Sada Mgalla has died at the age of 75.  Mama Sada Mgalla passed on at Diani Beach Hospital yesterday afternoon following a long illness and hard-fought battle with Oesophageal cancer.  The family said she will be buried today at Mavirivirini village in Kwale County.  President Uhuru Kenyatta mourned Mama Sada as a strong, virtuous and determined matriarch who raised an outstanding family.  In his tribute, Deputy President William Ruto described her as a humble, hardworking, God-fearing and responsible woman who raised upright children.  Joho, Mvurya, Kingi’s dilemma before exit  Mvurya cites bad weather for delay in building his residence  Governors seek to resolve boundary dispute  How budget got Governor Mvurya in trouble Baringo Senator Gideon Moi condoled with the family, describing Mama Sada as a humble and caring mother not only to her family but all those who interacted with her.    Mganga wa Kwale atibu vichaa na urogi  Supremacy battle pitting Zainab Chidzuga and governor Salim Mvurya plays out in public  CORD Leader Raila Odinga calls on the government to pay teachers  By Willis Oketch and Joackim Bwana | 8 hours ago By Patrick Beja | 1 day ago By Standard Team | 1 day ago By Tobias Chanji | 1 day ago